&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Housekeeper Acute Medical Unit LRI&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Acute Medical Unit at the Leicester Royal Infirmary are looking for a dynamic motivated housekeeper to work on a busy short stay unit. The AMU works closely with the new emergency floor. The patients admitted to the AMU are predominatly from the Emergency Department . Our patients stay is approximately 24 to 48 hours.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a valuable member of the ward team you will be responsible for maintaining a high standard of patient care at meal times and offer refreshments throughout their stay.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience in the care setting would be desirable but not essential. We are looking for enthusiastic individuals who are hard working with good communication and organisational skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will ensure the clinical environment is maintained to the appropriate standards. You will be instrumental in ensuring patients nutritional requirements are met.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should also have a positive attitude to change and be flexible. If you think you have the personality, motivation to join our team, this may be the opportunity you have been waiting for.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Internal Rotation Shifts will be required including weekends/ bank holidays.Shifts available are Earlies ,Late&#39;s or Long Days.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Vikki Davis&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sister in Emergency Care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;vikki.davis@uhl-tr.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
